<section xml:id="notes-week-03">
  <title>Week 3</title>

  <subsection>
    <title>Monday</title>
    <subsubsection xml:id="subsubsec-co-products">
      <title>Pullbacks and pushouts</title>
      <p>
        We will now consider (binary) pullbacks and pushouts. The product of sets <m>X,Y</m> is their Cartesian product
        <md>
          X\times Y = \{(x,y)\mid x\in X,y\in Y\}.
        </md>
        The coproduct of sets <m>X,Y</m> is their disjoint union
        <md>
          X\amalg Y = X\times \{0\} \cup Y\times \{1\}.
        </md>
        The function of <m>0</m> and <m>1</m> is to "color" the sets so that <m>(x,0)</m> and <m>(y,1)</m> remain distinct, even if <m>x=y</m>.
      </p>
      <p>
        These constructions come with special functions called projection and inclusion. On the product <m>X\times Y</m> we have 
        <m>\operatorname{pr}_X\colon X\times Y\to X</m> and <m>\operatorname{pr}_Y\colon X\times Y\to Y</m> given by 
        <m>\operatorname{pr}_X(x,y)=x</m> and <m>\operatorname{pr}_Y(x,y)=y</m>. Mapping into the corproduct <m>X\amalg Y</m> we have 
        <m>\operatornme{inc}_X\colon X\to X\amalg Y</m> and <m>\operatorname{inc}_Y\colon Y\to X\amalg Y</m> given by 
        <m>\operatorname{inc}_X(x) = (x,0)</m> and <m>\operatorname{inc}_Y(y) = (y,1)</m>.
      </p>
      <definition xml:id="def-co-prod">
        <title>(Co)product topologies by universal property</title>
        <statement>
        <p>
          Let <m>X,Y</m> be spaces. The <term>product</term> of <m>X</m> and <m>Y</m> is the space <m>X\times Y</m>
          satisfies the following universal property:
          <blockquote>
            <p>
              the projection maps <m>\operatorname{pr}_X</m> and <m>\operatorname{pr}_Y</m> are continuous and for any space <m>Z</m>, 
              a 
            </p>
          </blockquote>
          In this case, we call <m>q\colon X\to Z</m> a <term>quotient map</term>.
        </p>
      </statement>
      </definition>
    </subsubsection>

  </subsection>
